  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE..jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=506\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE..jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"720\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544641969\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_LPE..jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641953\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"53c28a16-381b-4406-b04e-be8d385643d4\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE..jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1800&amp;height=1012 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE..jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=506 1x\"></span><p /><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">In production, it often becomes necessary to create non-physical effects and art-directed changes to your shot. Light Path Expressions (LPE) are a powerful way to collect and output specific light paths for alteration later.</span><br/></p><p>Some examples of the power of LPE are the ability to:</p><ul><li><p>Allow for additive compositing, preserving the physical nature of the image and avoiding artifacts through multiplication or division in post-processing.</p></li><li><p>Output a specific bounce of light (2nd, 3rd, etc.) or even a range of bounces (4th to 8th bounce of light). You can use this to isolate effects or even noisy bounces for subtraction.</p></li><li><p>Output a specific object to an LPE. While you can use <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661911/PxrCryptomatte\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661911\" data-linked-resource-version=\"2\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Cryptomatte</a> to isolate objects with an ID, you can also output the object or collection of objects and their contribution separately.</p></li><li><p>Isolate a particular noisy light path for subtraction in comp or an LPE without these light paths to composite.</p></li><li><p>Create a non-physical effect like differently colored caustics from their source, change the color cast of an object or scale lighting.</p></li><li><p>Output per-light AOVs for manipulation later.</p></li></ul><p /><hr/><p /><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">In this example, we're going to create a LPE from an individual light in our studio scene.</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">First, select the light you want to create a Light and under the RenderMan tab → Light Group, create a name for your light groups.  Note, you can add more than one light into a light group to create various isolated lighting setups.</span></p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Node1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=475\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Node1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"676\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544641975\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Node1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641953\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"65fd87a1-326b-480c-9116-7ba442985f98\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Node1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1536&amp;height=811 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Node1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=475 1x\"></span><p /><hr/><p><br/><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">Next, we want to create the actual LPE expression to be able to isolate this light in our AOV channels.  </span></p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"renderVarLOP.png\" width=\"964\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/renderVarLOP.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057332908&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=964&amp;height=748\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641953/renderVarLOP.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057332908&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"748\" data-width=\"964\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"662798531\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"renderVarLOP.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641953\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"8d26d41c-1a7f-4750-a6cc-7f8af0eb6eb9\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/renderVarLOP.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057332908&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=964&amp;height=748 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/renderVarLOP.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057332908&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=964&amp;height=748 1x\"></span><p><br/>Using a Render Var LOP<span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">, you will there be able to enter in the desired information to create the LPE.  As you can see, the LPE will be called SideRoom_LPE and the source name defines the structure of the LPE and also included in the expression is the SideRoomLight, which refers to our previously created Light Group.</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">More information on LPE expressions can be found </span><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661899/Using+LPE\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661899\" data-linked-resource-version=\"3\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span style=\"color: rgb(23,43,77);\">here</span></a><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">.</span></p><p>Simply connecting the Render Var LOP to the first input of the RenderMan Render Settings LOP will be enough for the created Render Product primitive to add it to the <em>orderedVars</em> attribute (as shown below in the Scene Graph).</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"renderVarSceneGraph.png\" width=\"941\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/renderVarSceneGraph.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057494459&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=941&amp;height=387\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641953/renderVarSceneGraph.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057494459&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"387\" data-width=\"941\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"665714710\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"renderVarSceneGraph.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641953\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"ffb4fa5c-ac40-4710-a8ad-ab3310a57540\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/renderVarSceneGraph.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057494459&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=941&amp;height=387 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/renderVarSceneGraph.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1763057494459&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=941&amp;height=387 1x\"></span><p>The image below demonstrates the SideRoomLight LPE contribution.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Room.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=506\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Room.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"720\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544641972\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Room.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641953\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"22e4a302-ff32-4153-a92d-0b15f995a682\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Room.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1800&amp;height=1012 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641953/RenderMan_Solaris_LPE_Room.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433095965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=506 1x\"></span><p />"
    }
  },
